  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is an etching by Karel Dujardin (c. 1626–1678), serving as the **title page (frontispiece) for the series \"Dieren\" (Animals)** — a set of 8 etchings of pastoral animal subjects, all dated 1652. It is cataloged as **Hollstein 1** (Hollstein VI, p. 29, no. 1), **Bartsch 1**, and **Dutuit IV.1** — the very first entry in Dujardin's cataloged etched oeuvre. Dujardin both made and published this series himself.",
